WEBVTT

00:00.159 --> 00:02.391
<i>Previously on "Bates Motel"...</i>

00:02.392 --> 00:04.645
I am dead. And why am I
pretending to be dead?

00:04.646 --> 00:06.476
So I could get away from everyone,

00:06.477 --> 00:08.535
everything that could
distract me from you.

00:08.536 --> 00:10.277
Oh, hi.

00:10.278 --> 00:12.376
- <i>Who is she?</i>
- Mother, she's married.

00:12.377 --> 00:14.060
You can't have other
people in your life,

00:14.061 --> 00:15.265
especially women.

00:15.266 --> 00:17.013
I need a room for a few hours.

00:17.014 --> 00:20.365
- Your name?
- David... Davidson.

00:20.366 --> 00:22.156
<i>Do let me know if I can
do anything else for you,</i>

00:22.157 --> 00:23.829
<i>Mr. David Davidson.</i>

00:24.492 --> 00:26.406
<i>I was sorry to hear
your parole got denied.</i>

00:26.407 --> 00:28.066
Two more years... that's
all I care about.

00:28.067 --> 00:29.696
Mother, I have someone else's wallet,

00:29.697 --> 00:31.026
and I don't know how I got it.

00:31.027 --> 00:32.485
<i>Do you ever have the feeling</i>

00:32.487 --> 00:33.986
<i>that you've had the same nightmare</i>

00:33.987 --> 00:35.566
<i>over and over again,</i>

00:35.567 --> 00:37.066
<i>but that you can't remember it?</i>

00:37.067 --> 00:38.026
- (CELL PHONE RINGING)
- Turn it off.

00:38.027 --> 00:39.327
Someone's gonna hear you.

00:40.447 --> 00:42.236
<i>Jim?</i>

00:42.237 --> 00:44.116
Jim?

00:44.117 --> 00:45.867
<i>Y-you there?</i>

00:48.067 --> 00:50.946
<i>(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING ON CAR RADIO)</i>

00:50.947 --> 00:57.867
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:02.197 --> 01:04.486
<i>Those thunder bumpers have
finally left the area.</i>

01:04.486 --> 01:07.826
<i>It is 68 degrees and
partly sunny in Bend,</i>

01:07.827 --> 01:10.736
<i>with another chance of rain on Saturday.</i>

01:10.737 --> 01:12.776
<i>This is a weather pattern that
is looking to really continue</i>

01:12.777 --> 01:14.406
<i>over the next couple of days.</i>

01:14.407 --> 01:15.736
<i>High pressure building...</i>

01:15.737 --> 01:18.736
<i>(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC)</i>

01:18.737 --> 01:25.617
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:30.367 --> 01:31.904
Romero.

01:32.967 --> 01:34.407
You've got a visitor.

01:36.827 --> 01:39.567
(BUZZER BLARES)

01:44.367 --> 01:47.366
<i>(DARK MUSIC)</i>

01:47.367 --> 01:54.237
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:57.597 --> 01:59.017
Hey, Sheriff.

02:00.381 --> 02:01.461
How's life?

02:04.641 --> 02:09.220
Oh, I'm here because you
were worried about me.

02:09.221 --> 02:11.800
It was really kind of
you to send your friend

02:11.801 --> 02:14.010
to see how I'd been getting along.

02:14.011 --> 02:16.341
But as you can see, I'm quite all right.

02:18.721 --> 02:19.970
You are, huh?

02:19.971 --> 02:23.550
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:23.551 --> 02:25.380
You know something?

02:25.381 --> 02:27.550
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:27.551 --> 02:30.550
Don't think I am unsympathetic
to your plight.

02:30.551 --> 02:32.550
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:32.551 --> 02:35.340
I know what it's like to
be locked up somewhere

02:35.341 --> 02:37.760
and being watched all the time,

02:37.761 --> 02:40.340
because you put me in such a
place... do you remember?

02:40.341 --> 02:41.590
That was your mother's decision.

02:41.591 --> 02:43.180
Uh-uh. Don't lie.

02:43.181 --> 02:45.260
That is a lie. It... it was you.

02:45.261 --> 02:47.260
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:47.261 --> 02:48.880
It was you.

02:48.881 --> 02:52.010
It was your way of
trying to get rid of me.

02:52.011 --> 02:55.050
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:55.051 --> 02:57.510
And I'm still alive.

02:57.511 --> 02:58.840
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:58.841 --> 03:00.340
For now.

03:00.341 --> 03:03.090
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:03.091 --> 03:04.680
Great seeing you, Sheriff.

03:04.681 --> 03:07.300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:07.301 --> 03:08.880
Mm.

03:08.881 --> 03:11.050
I'm coming for you when
you least expect it,

03:11.051 --> 03:12.680
so don't get too cozy

03:12.681 --> 03:14.840
up at that house all by yourself.

03:14.841 --> 03:21.761
