10:52.417 --> 10:55.564
<i>♪ Don't know much about algebra ♪</i>

10:56.144 --> 10:59.484
<i>♪ Don't know what a slide rule is for ♪</i>

10:59.485 --> 11:03.104
<i>♪ But I do know one and one is two ♪</i>

11:03.105 --> 11:04.984
<i>♪ And if this one could be... ♪</i>

11:04.985 --> 11:07.894
<i>(SOMBER ORCHESTRAL MUSIC)</i>

11:07.895 --> 11:14.815
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:25.275 --> 11:32.145
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:38.865 --> 11:40.115
Norman?

11:41.583 --> 11:44.212
Oh. Oh, Madeleine.

11:44.213 --> 11:46.753
(CHUCKLES) It's, uh, so good to see you.

11:46.754 --> 11:49.214
D-do you get some coffee here, too?

11:49.215 --> 11:50.795
Well, yeah. It...

11:50.796 --> 11:52.336
it's right across the street.

11:52.337 --> 11:53.757
I guess it is.

11:53.758 --> 11:55.087
Hey, I'm sorry you couldn't come

11:55.088 --> 11:56.837
to the meeting, but I can fill you in

11:56.838 --> 11:58.507
on all the ideas that came out of it...

11:58.508 --> 11:59.877
a lot of them about preserving

11:59.878 --> 12:02.087
the architectural
history of the village.

12:02.088 --> 12:04.427
Well, I-I love that...

12:04.428 --> 12:06.757
preserving the architectural history

12:06.758 --> 12:08.637
of the village.

12:08.638 --> 12:15.337
♪ ♪

12:15.338 --> 12:17.587
Hey, can I be really nosy
and pushy for a second?

12:17.588 --> 12:19.637
And if you hate it, you
can tell me to stop.

12:19.638 --> 12:20.877
Okay?

12:20.878 --> 12:22.257
Okay.

12:22.258 --> 12:23.427
♪ ♪

12:23.428 --> 12:25.156
Can I set you up with someone?

12:26.798 --> 12:29.137
Oh. Uh...

12:29.138 --> 12:31.110
I don't really do that
sort of thing, you know.

12:31.111 --> 12:32.111
I get it.

12:32.112 --> 12:33.927
I really do.

12:33.928 --> 12:35.967
You know, the truth is, I
just thought it would be fun

12:35.968 --> 12:37.377
for all of us.

12:37.378 --> 12:39.297
Oh. (STAMMERS) All of us?

12:39.298 --> 12:40.967
Yeah.

12:40.968 --> 12:43.087
I've gotten to know
this nice girl, Joanne.

12:43.088 --> 12:45.337
She's helping me with my store Website.

12:45.338 --> 12:49.427
She's single and says
she never meets anyone.

12:49.428 --> 12:52.927
She's really cute and nice, and
you're really cute and nice.

12:52.928 --> 12:55.191
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:55.192 --> 12:57.467
My husband doesn't
know many people here,

12:57.468 --> 12:59.614
and I'm trying to get him to
see how cool this place is

12:59.928 --> 13:03.967
and, you know, meet the locals.

13:03.968 --> 13:05.797
I thought it would be a win-win.

13:05.798 --> 13:08.437
And a chance for us to get to
know each other better, too.

13:09.088 --> 13:10.407
What do you think?

13:11.878 --> 13:15.545
Well, I think if you're
going, then it's different.

13:15.968 --> 13:20.007
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:20.429 --> 13:22.772
You're a bit of a flirt, aren't you?

13:23.468 --> 13:26.257
- Am I?
- Yeah. You are.

13:26.258 --> 13:28.547
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:28.548 --> 13:30.007
Hey, babe, what's taking so long?

13:30.008 --> 13:31.967
Yeah, sorry. I just got caught up.

13:31.968 --> 13:33.362
This is Norman Bates.

13:33.363 --> 13:36.547
He owns the Bates Motel
right outside the village.

13:37.920 --> 13:39.606
It's nice to meet you.

13:39.607 --> 13:41.837
Uh, what was the name?

13:44.126 --> 13:45.377
Sam Loomis.

13:45.690 --> 13:48.013
Nice to meet you, Sam Loomis.

13:49.508 --> 13:52.245
I'm setting Norman up
with Joanne Carlson.

13:52.675 --> 13:54.298
Who's Joanne Carlson?

13:54.968 --> 13:56.547
You know, that woman

13:56.548 --> 13:58.757
who's been totally
redesigning our Website?

13:58.758 --> 14:01.150
- Oh, right.
- You met her, like, twice.

14:01.787 --> 14:03.757
Sam's head is still in Seattle.

14:03.758 --> 14:05.637
Oh. My business is there.

14:05.638 --> 14:07.427
I'm finishing up some
real estate development.

14:07.428 --> 14:09.637
Oh. Sounds exciting, Sam.

14:09.638 --> 14:11.467
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:11.468 --> 14:14.217
See? We're gonna have
so much to talk about.

14:14.218 --> 14:15.637
Let's... Why don't we say tonight?

14:15.638 --> 14:18.166
Say, 7:00 at the Temple Street Bar?

14:18.638 --> 14:20.377
I would love to have dinner with you,

14:20.378 --> 14:21.739
meet your friend.

14:22.339 --> 14:24.177
Great. It's a date.

14:24.645 --> 14:25.732
Great.

14:25.733 --> 14:27.257
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:27.258 --> 14:29.006
Bye.

14:29.007 --> 14:30.967
- See you later.
- See you.

14:30.968 --> 14:33.717
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

14:33.718 --> 14:35.047
Hi.

14:35.048 --> 14:41.108
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:52.008 --> 14:53.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:53.718 --> 14:55.641
Hey. How do you feel?

14:57.048 --> 14:58.717
Swell.

14:58.718 --> 15:01.717
Do you know your name?

15:01.718 --> 15:04.467
D-do you know yours?

15:04.468 --> 15:07.637
I know that I don't have a concussion.

15:07.638 --> 15:11.637
Alex Romero, inmate number A49452...

15:11.638 --> 15:14.950
cellblock five, cage 63.

15:15.468 --> 15:19.587
I'm serving five years on a
trumped-up perjury beef.

15:19.588 --> 15:20.744
What happened?

15:21.148 --> 15:22.728
Did someone find out you're a cop?

15:25.138 --> 15:26.928
Yeah, apparently.

15:29.088 --> 15:32.056
Can't hide the truth
forever. Inmates talk.

15:32.838 --> 15:36.303
Found out I was an ex-cop and jumped me.

15:36.304 --> 15:40.337
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:40.642 --> 15:42.831
Uh, maybe I need to talk to my lawyer.

15:44.451 --> 15:45.614
I would.

15:46.008 --> 15:51.982
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:11.798 --> 16:14.137
<i>COMPUTER VOICE: Le livre
est sur la table.</i>

16:14.138 --> 16:16.297
<i>Le livre est sur la table.</i>

16:16.298 --> 16:18.377
Mother? Who are you talking to?

16:18.378 --> 16:21.427
Hi, Norman. I'm studying French.

16:21.428 --> 16:24.330
<i>The bedroom is blue.</i>
La chambre est bleu.

16:24.331 --> 16:25.837
<i>La chambre est bleu.</i>

16:25.838 --> 16:27.837
Why?

16:27.838 --> 16:30.177
Oh, I figure just because
I'm trapped in this house

16:30.178 --> 16:32.124
doesn't mean my mind has to stagnate.

16:32.928 --> 16:35.507
<i>Red.</i> Rouge.

16:35.508 --> 16:37.217
<i>Rouge.</i>

16:37.218 --> 16:40.217
<i>The cherry is red.</i> La cerise est rouge.

16:40.218 --> 16:42.377
<i>La cerise est rouge.</i>

16:42.378 --> 16:44.467
By the way, where have you been all day?

16:44.468 --> 16:46.217
I was up at 7:00. You were already gone.

16:46.218 --> 16:48.758
Oh, yeah. I just had a
few errands to run.

16:50.758 --> 16:54.587
Oh, in fact, I should maybe
get back to the office.

16:54.588 --> 16:57.378
<i>Traitor.</i> Traître.

16:59.218 --> 17:00.582
<i>Traître.</i>

17:00.583 --> 17:04.637
<i>The traitor was hung.</i>
Le traître a été pend...

17:04.637 --> 17:06.606
What kind of French course is this?

17:09.258 --> 17:11.244
- Where were you really today?
- The village.

17:11.246 --> 17:13.077
For six hours?

17:16.538 --> 17:18.676
I went to see Romero in prison.

17:18.678 --> 17:20.047
Why?

17:20.048 --> 17:21.547
To tell him that you
know he sent someone

17:21.548 --> 17:23.047
to kill you and you're still alive?

17:23.048 --> 17:25.637
- Basically, yes.
- That's kind of dumb.

17:25.637 --> 17:26.837
I mean, wouldn't it be better

17:26.838 --> 17:27.797
to let him think that you're dead

17:27.798 --> 17:29.337
so he leaves you alone?

17:29.338 --> 17:30.837
Mother, he is going to get out someday,

17:30.838 --> 17:32.677
and we have to deal with it.

17:32.678 --> 17:34.337
He thinks that I killed you, remember?

17:34.338 --> 17:36.507
He is crazy, and so I
just went to make sure

17:36.508 --> 17:38.927
he was never gonna mess
with me ever again.

17:38.928 --> 17:40.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:40.380 --> 17:42.337
I can handle him when he gets out.

17:42.338 --> 17:44.297
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:44.298 --> 17:46.797
Are... are you saying
you're gonna kill him?

17:46.798 --> 17:51.047
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:51.048 --> 17:53.547
Mother, do you still
have feelings for him?

17:53.548 --> 17:54.587
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:54.588 --> 17:56.507
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

17:56.508 --> 17:58.007
Hello!

17:58.008 --> 17:59.797
Norman?

17:59.798 --> 18:02.137
- (SIGHS) It's just Chick.
- (GROANS) That guy.

18:02.138 --> 18:03.731
He's so annoying.

18:03.732 --> 18:06.007
- I have to hide every time he comes over.
- (DOORBELL RINGING)

18:06.008 --> 18:07.797
I know, Mother, but he's
been nice to me, okay?

18:07.798 --> 18:09.671
He's helped me out with
things around the house.

18:09.672 --> 18:10.829
Norman?

18:10.830 --> 18:11.849
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:11.850 --> 18:13.877
Coming!

18:13.878 --> 18:16.257
And besides, okay, it's necessary

18:16.258 --> 18:17.757
to have one friend from the outside.

18:17.758 --> 18:19.047
It makes things look more normal.

18:19.048 --> 18:20.137
You just got to deal with it.

18:20.138 --> 18:22.337
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:22.338 --> 18:23.967
Pretending to be dead isn't as much fun

18:23.968 --> 18:25.257
as I thought it would be.

18:25.258 --> 18:27.967
(DOOR CLOSES)

18:27.968 --> 18:30.507
- Hey. Sorry, Chick.
- Yeah.

18:30.508 --> 18:33.217
I just came by to check on you.

18:33.218 --> 18:35.111
Is it a bad time?

18:36.008 --> 18:38.427
Mm. Never mind. It's just an expression.

18:38.428 --> 18:40.935
I'm here. I brought these for you.

18:41.588 --> 18:43.211
They're... they're fresh.

18:44.298 --> 18:46.547
Well, they... they look delicious.

18:47.000 --> 18:48.587
Thank you so much.

18:48.588 --> 18:50.493
Yeah, they're Lady Annes.

18:51.546 --> 18:53.007
I picked them from my neighbor's tree.

18:53.008 --> 18:53.801
(CHUCKLES)

18:55.508 --> 18:58.337
Moving out of that place.
He can't afford it.

18:58.338 --> 19:00.087
So I thought, "You got to pick

19:00.088 --> 19:02.174
while the picking's good," right?

19:02.678 --> 19:04.177
- That's what you got to do.
- Yeah.

19:04.178 --> 19:06.137
Thank you. Thank you, Chick.

19:06.138 --> 19:07.967
- Yeah.
- Really.

19:07.968 --> 19:10.587
It's just... that's
actually not why I...

19:10.588 --> 19:11.934
why I came.

19:13.378 --> 19:15.087
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:15.088 --> 19:17.257
I wanted to show you something.

19:17.258 --> 19:18.467
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:18.468 --> 19:21.507
Go on. Take a look.

19:21.508 --> 19:25.547
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:25.548 --> 19:28.507
I have a business proposition for you.

19:28.508 --> 19:30.177
(CRUNCHES)

19:30.178 --> 19:32.587
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:32.588 --> 19:34.677
Let's go in the basement!

19:34.678 --> 19:37.137
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:37.138 --> 19:39.007
The basement it is!

19:39.008 --> 19:44.878
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:50.747 --> 19:52.524
It's a peregrine.

19:52.957 --> 19:55.786
Fastest-moving creature on record.

19:55.787 --> 19:57.909
Still pretty rare, though.

19:58.657 --> 20:00.457
She's stunning.

20:02.957 --> 20:04.866
So here's what I'm thinking.

20:05.867 --> 20:09.827
I bring you these, uh, specimens...

20:12.247 --> 20:16.416
And you, uh, turn 'em into art.

20:16.417 --> 20:17.987
Then I help you sell 'em.

20:18.867 --> 20:20.953
You really think someone will buy them?

20:22.077 --> 20:23.656
You got quite a talent.

20:23.657 --> 20:26.156
Your technique is superlative.

20:26.157 --> 20:28.246
I know an art dealer in Portland

20:28.247 --> 20:31.536
who specializes in the un-commonalities.

20:31.537 --> 20:34.537
She's showcased some of my work.

20:36.287 --> 20:37.916
Well, it would be nice

20:37.917 --> 20:39.996
for others to appreciate
these beautiful animals,

20:39.997 --> 20:42.998
and I could sure use the space.

20:44.827 --> 20:48.286
So we'll... we'll do a 50/50 split.

20:48.287 --> 20:50.157
50/50?

20:53.003 --> 20:55.156
(STAMMERS) Look, I...

20:55.157 --> 20:58.286
normally, an art dealer gets
50 just for showing the piece.

20:58.287 --> 21:01.496
I'm getting 50 by bringing
you the specimens,

21:01.497 --> 21:02.826
by repping you,

21:02.827 --> 21:05.867
plus providing you the art dealer.

21:08.117 --> 21:12.157
The fact of the matter is, is that I...

21:14.997 --> 21:17.262
I'm broke.

21:18.208 --> 21:21.709
Caleb crippled my hands and my body.

21:23.088 --> 21:24.824
I can't work on my own.

21:26.287 --> 21:28.089
I need the money, Norman.

21:28.960 --> 21:30.457
I understand.

21:33.327 --> 21:36.392
How's that freezer working out for you?

21:37.157 --> 21:38.616
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

21:38.617 --> 21:40.984
It's working much better.

21:41.787 --> 21:43.916
Thanks for fixing it. It's staying cold.

21:44.432 --> 21:46.116
That's good to hear.

21:46.117 --> 21:50.812
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:51.957 --> 21:54.206
A pair of Eurasian jays.

21:54.207 --> 21:55.246
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:55.247 --> 21:56.826
Beautiful.

21:56.827 --> 21:58.366
So we'll give this a go, then?

21:58.367 --> 21:59.996
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:59.997 --> 22:01.332
Partner?

22:01.867 --> 22:04.656
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:04.657 --> 22:06.247
We'll give it a go.

22:06.997 --> 22:09.327
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:18.917 --> 22:21.747
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

22:25.157 --> 22:26.746
- Hey.
- Hey.

22:26.747 --> 22:29.286
Welcome to the Kings Motel.

22:29.287 --> 22:31.156
What brings you to town?

22:31.157 --> 22:33.996
- I'm just visiting my sister.
- Of course.

22:33.997 --> 22:36.616
Uh, which credit card
will you be using today?

22:36.617 --> 22:39.866
- Uh, cash.
- Cash is fine.

22:39.867 --> 22:42.206
All right.

22:42.207 --> 22:44.116
(CLEARS THROAT) Who's your sister?

22:44.117 --> 22:46.326
Norma Bates.

22:46.327 --> 22:48.959
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:49.747 --> 22:51.246
What?

22:51.247 --> 22:52.786
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:52.787 --> 22:54.496
Um, when was the last
time you talked to her?

22:54.497 --> 22:56.156
I don't know. Like, a
year and a half ago.

22:56.157 --> 22:57.866
I've been out of the country. Why?

22:57.867 --> 22:59.496
Right, um...

22:59.497 --> 23:01.656
Uh, I hate to be the
one to tell you this,

23:01.657 --> 23:06.456
but your sister... she,
uh... she passed away.

23:06.457 --> 23:08.206
It was a terrible tragedy.

23:08.207 --> 23:09.996
What are you talking
about? No, she didn't.

23:09.997 --> 23:12.536
I was just with her son. He
would've said something.

23:12.537 --> 23:14.614
<i>(SOMBER MUSIC)</i>

23:15.037 --> 23:17.076
I don't know what to tell you.

23:17.077 --> 23:18.916
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:18.917 --> 23:21.496
Look, she... she died.
She committed suicide.

23:21.497 --> 23:23.416
It made the local news.

23:23.417 --> 23:25.156
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:25.157 --> 23:27.366
I'm so sorry you had to
hear about it this way.

23:27.367 --> 23:31.076
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:31.077 --> 23:34.036
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

23:34.037 --> 23:39.327
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:40.957 --> 23:42.997
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

23:52.607 --> 23:54.607
Ah, Mr. Davidson.

23:56.247 --> 23:58.996
You need a room again for a few hours?

23:58.997 --> 24:01.417
No. I came to see you.

24:03.537 --> 24:04.866
This double date...

24:05.997 --> 24:07.970
I just came by to see...

24:08.457 --> 24:10.411
what kind of a man you are.

24:11.397 --> 24:14.958
I'm not sure we have the
same dictionary definition.

24:15.457 --> 24:18.866
I'm not gonna stand here
and explain myself to you.

24:18.867 --> 24:20.869
All I can tell you is...

24:21.537 --> 24:23.117
stay out of it.

24:26.390 --> 24:28.866
Well, you're right. It's
none of my business.

24:29.787 --> 24:32.319
I barely know you or your wife.

24:34.764 --> 24:37.811
But man-to-man,

24:37.812 --> 24:40.563
Sam, you don't care
much for her, do you?

24:42.747 --> 24:46.275
See, the thing is,
Norman, I'm a nice guy.

24:47.537 --> 24:51.996
I am, but in spite of that,
I'm perfectly willing

24:51.997 --> 24:54.036
to kick your ass across
that gravel out there

24:54.037 --> 24:57.247
if you breathe a word
about this to my wife.

24:59.367 --> 25:01.497
Do we understand each other?

25:04.207 --> 25:05.428
I think so.

25:06.657 --> 25:08.054
Don't screw with me.

25:08.577 --> 25:12.656
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:12.657 --> 25:14.135
(DOOR CLOSES)

25:15.417 --> 25:22.367
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:30.917 --> 25:37.827
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:00.497 --> 26:07.417
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:19.577 --> 26:22.576
(SOBBING)

26:22.577 --> 26:29.497
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:37.457 --> 26:40.286
<i>(EDITH PIAF'S "LA VIE EN
ROSE" PLAYING ON STEREO)</i>

26:40.287 --> 26:47.207
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:50.837 --> 26:52.716
Mother, are you smoking?

26:52.717 --> 26:55.496
I'm dead. It's not like
it's gonna kill me.

26:55.497 --> 26:56.956
Don't do that. I'm bored.

26:56.957 --> 26:59.156
- I can smoke if I want to.
- No, you can't.

26:59.157 --> 27:02.616
You can't smoke. You're
just trying to punish me.

27:02.617 --> 27:03.956
(SCOFFS)

27:03.957 --> 27:06.326
Seriously, Mother, it's childish.

27:06.327 --> 27:13.247
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:18.157 --> 27:21.246
Is this silliness because we
were talking about Romero?

27:21.950 --> 27:23.076
No.

27:23.077 --> 27:25.366
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:25.367 --> 27:26.456
What?

27:26.855 --> 27:28.488
Do you still love him?

27:28.997 --> 27:29.996
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:29.997 --> 27:31.246
No.

27:31.247 --> 27:32.706
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:32.707 --> 27:33.996
He sent someone here to kill me.

27:33.997 --> 27:35.956
You remember that, right?

27:35.957 --> 27:38.576
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:38.577 --> 27:41.956
(INHALES DEEPLY)

27:41.957 --> 27:45.076
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:45.077 --> 27:46.635
Where are you going?

27:46.636 --> 27:48.206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:48.207 --> 27:49.641
Business meeting.

27:50.639 --> 27:53.451
You seem really into
business meetings lately.

27:53.452 --> 27:55.496
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:55.497 --> 27:57.616
Please don't be childish,
Mother. It's boring.

27:57.617 --> 28:00.286
It's important for us to keep
a presence in the community.

28:00.287 --> 28:02.416
And I didn't even go to the last one.

28:02.417 --> 28:04.956
- We were busy, as you may recall.
- I recall.

28:04.957 --> 28:09.866
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:09.867 --> 28:11.677
I'll be back in a few hours,

28:13.077 --> 28:14.366
and we'll spend some time together.

28:14.367 --> 28:15.366
I promise.

28:15.367 --> 28:16.826
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:16.827 --> 28:18.246
Just don't get yourself in such a state,

28:18.247 --> 28:19.326
listening to this music.

28:19.327 --> 28:21.366
- And don't smoke.
- Okay.

28:21.367 --> 28:27.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:27.417 --> 28:30.326
<i>(PIAF SINGING IN FRENCH)</i>

28:30.327 --> 28:32.076
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:32.077 --> 28:34.576
(ENGINE TURNING OVER)

28:34.577 --> 28:41.497
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:56.164 --> 28:58.404
I started in the theater department.

28:58.405 --> 29:00.945
I wanted to be a stage
actor more than anything,

29:00.946 --> 29:03.275
but I never got cast,

29:03.276 --> 29:05.355
and my dad kept telling me that
no one was going to cast me

29:05.356 --> 29:06.905
and I needed another job.

29:06.906 --> 29:08.145
He said that the last
thing this world needs

29:08.146 --> 29:09.525
is another actor,

29:09.526 --> 29:12.355
and I was like, "Thanks, asshole."

29:12.356 --> 29:13.985
(CHUCKLES) Parents don't always know.

29:13.986 --> 29:15.735
Mine didn't.

29:15.736 --> 29:17.937
We don't talk anymore. He's a dick.

29:19.523 --> 29:22.525
So, uh, then you decided to go

29:22.526 --> 29:25.315
- into computer programming.
- Yeah.

29:25.316 --> 29:27.855
I don't really like it, but
I'm kind of good at it, so...

29:27.856 --> 29:30.085
You're amazing at it.

29:30.086 --> 29:32.235
Norman, you should see the
Website she's making for us.

29:32.236 --> 29:34.815
Oh. It's easy with you. You're artistic.

29:34.816 --> 29:37.645
Oh, I know she is, just
from being in her shop.

29:37.646 --> 29:40.419
Uh... our shop.

29:40.420 --> 29:41.195
Mm.

29:41.196 --> 29:43.695
Yes, of course, Sam. It's
just, you're never there.

29:44.138 --> 29:46.395
Well, my business is in Seattle.

29:46.396 --> 29:47.855
It wasn't my idea to move,

29:47.856 --> 29:50.355
but we're getting it figured out.

29:50.356 --> 29:52.378
I know. We will.

29:54.462 --> 29:56.751
Oh! Oh, and we're out.

29:56.752 --> 29:58.751
Oh. Uh, excuse me.

29:58.752 --> 30:01.522
Could we get another bottle
of the Château de Maragrite?

30:01.523 --> 30:03.443
You have such a good French accent.

30:03.444 --> 30:04.847
Do you speak French?

30:06.372 --> 30:08.791
Oh, no. Uh, no, my...

30:08.792 --> 30:12.171
I just listen to French
movies sometimes.

30:12.172 --> 30:13.711
- With subtitles?
- Mm-hmm.

30:13.712 --> 30:15.371
I hate subtitles. I'm like,

30:15.372 --> 30:16.581
"Am I watching this or
reading it?" You know?

30:16.582 --> 30:17.671
Yeah, I don't have the patience

30:17.672 --> 30:20.291
to get through most movies.

30:20.292 --> 30:22.461
I guess I'm more of a doer.

30:22.462 --> 30:24.501
What is it you're always doing, Sam?

30:24.502 --> 30:26.921
(JAZZY PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

30:26.922 --> 30:28.041
Real estate.

30:28.042 --> 30:30.580
♪ ♪

30:30.581 --> 30:33.291
Sam's working on a couple
of houses he's flipping.

30:33.292 --> 30:35.371
Oh, that's right. House flipping.

30:35.372 --> 30:37.001
He made some good money from it,

30:37.002 --> 30:39.001
but he knows the market
way better in Seattle

30:39.002 --> 30:40.581
than the market here.

30:40.582 --> 30:43.211
So, as a result, I spend a lot of time

30:43.212 --> 30:46.001
at the hardware store by myself.

30:46.002 --> 30:49.131
- You can handle it.
- Yeah, I can.

30:49.132 --> 30:51.447
It's all gonna be good.

30:51.448 --> 30:54.211
♪ ♪

30:54.212 --> 30:55.751
My mother used to say that.

30:55.752 --> 30:57.331
<i>(SOMBER MUSIC)</i>

30:57.332 --> 30:58.671
She did?

30:58.672 --> 31:00.780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:00.781 --> 31:02.500
Well, she was right.

31:02.501 --> 31:03.541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:03.542 --> 31:06.871
I heard about your mother. I'm sorry.

31:06.872 --> 31:07.961
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:07.962 --> 31:09.371
What happened?

31:09.372 --> 31:11.152
She passed away not too long ago.

31:11.962 --> 31:13.581
She killed herself.

31:13.582 --> 31:15.211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:15.212 --> 31:16.898
Oh. I'm sorry.

31:17.825 --> 31:20.371
Thanks. It's, uh...

31:20.372 --> 31:22.001
It was a while ago.

31:22.002 --> 31:24.501
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:24.502 --> 31:27.211
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

31:27.212 --> 31:29.961
I'm really glad you came out tonight.

31:29.962 --> 31:37.131
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:37.132 --> 31:39.921
Thank you. I'll, uh...
I'll be right back.

31:39.922 --> 31:42.331
(RAGGED BREATHING)

31:42.332 --> 31:45.252
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:53.672 --> 31:55.985
Business meeting, huh?

31:57.372 --> 31:59.921
For the love of God, Mother,
what are you doing here?

31:59.922 --> 32:02.331
I could just as easily
ask you that question.

32:02.332 --> 32:04.291
Mother, I am not the one
who's supposed to be dead.

32:04.292 --> 32:06.291
I mean, what if someone saw you in here?

32:06.292 --> 32:08.042
No one did. It's fine.

32:09.712 --> 32:11.671
By the way...

32:11.672 --> 32:14.291
when did you start lying to me?

32:14.292 --> 32:15.711
I'm not lying to you, Mother.

32:15.712 --> 32:18.081
I just got trapped into
coming to this dinner.

32:18.082 --> 32:20.831
Okay? Madeleine wanted
me to meet her friend.

32:20.832 --> 32:22.371
I've got no interest in her friend,

32:22.372 --> 32:23.791
but I didn't want to be rude.

32:23.792 --> 32:26.041
It just seemed easier
to go to the dinner

32:26.042 --> 32:28.711
than insult her.

32:28.712 --> 32:31.331
Well, I'm glad you're thinking
of everyone else's feelings.

32:31.332 --> 32:33.131
Mother, you're overreacting, okay?

32:33.132 --> 32:35.251
But right now you need to leave.

32:35.252 --> 32:37.041
Come on. Let's go.

32:37.042 --> 32:39.001
Let's go, Mother. Out.

32:39.002 --> 32:41.291
We can't risk you walking
back through the restaurant.

32:41.292 --> 32:42.711
- That is ridiculous.
- No, Mother.

32:42.712 --> 32:45.131
What's ridiculous is a dead woman

32:45.132 --> 32:47.331
walking through a restaurant
where she might be spotted

32:47.332 --> 32:48.791
by any number of people who know her.

32:48.792 --> 32:49.921
I didn't see any people I know.

32:49.922 --> 32:51.331
- I looked.
- Mother!

32:51.332 --> 32:53.671
(SILENTLY) Just go out the window now.

32:53.672 --> 32:56.631
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

32:56.632 --> 32:57.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:57.832 --> 32:59.921
Take the keys.

32:59.922 --> 33:01.671
Get in the back of the car

33:01.672 --> 33:03.251
and lay down so no one can see you.

33:03.252 --> 33:06.331
I will be done with dinner
soon. Just wait for me.

33:06.332 --> 33:09.671
Norman, do you still like me?

33:09.672 --> 33:12.631
<i>(SOMBER MUSIC)</i>

33:12.632 --> 33:16.831
Yes. Mother, yes. I still like you.

33:16.832 --> 33:18.331
Now go!

33:18.332 --> 33:25.252
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:30.332 --> 33:33.251
<i>(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)</i>

33:33.252 --> 33:34.632
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:36.287 --> 33:38.326
Given what happened...

33:38.327 --> 33:39.826
I can go to a circuit judge

33:39.827 --> 33:41.366
and effectively argue that your life

33:41.367 --> 33:43.956
is in jeopardy in here
and that it was punitive

33:43.957 --> 33:45.866
to ever put you in a
medium-security prison

33:45.867 --> 33:47.616
based on a perjury charge.

33:48.071 --> 33:50.030
I should be able to get
you to a work farm.

33:50.031 --> 33:51.616
Okay. Well, I'd like to be moved.

33:51.617 --> 33:53.206
I... Uh...

33:53.207 --> 33:54.826
When I came here, I was so devastated

33:54.827 --> 33:56.406
about losing my wife, I didn't care,

33:56.407 --> 33:58.996
but now it's... I-I need
to stay alive and well.

33:58.997 --> 34:01.456
I have a responsibility to...

34:01.457 --> 34:03.616
to take care of the son
that she left behind.

34:03.617 --> 34:05.956
So, yeah, I'd... I'd
like to be transferred.

34:05.957 --> 34:07.286
I'll file the transfer request.

34:07.287 --> 34:11.326
- Okay.
- Until then, just relax.

34:11.327 --> 34:13.956
For God's sake, try not to
piss a anybody else off.

34:13.956 --> 34:16.367
- I'll do my best.
- All right.

34:20.746 --> 34:23.616
<i>(FOREBODING MUSIC)</i>

34:23.617 --> 34:26.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:26.167 --> 34:27.536
Good-bye.

34:27.536 --> 34:30.456
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:30.456 --> 34:32.366
Thank you.

34:32.367 --> 34:34.616
I'm sorry about that.

34:34.617 --> 34:41.536
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:45.407 --> 34:49.206
(MUFFLED INDISTINCT CHATTER)

34:49.206 --> 34:50.826
It was fun, though. It
was good to see you.

34:50.827 --> 34:52.496
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:52.496 --> 34:53.826
Why aren't you starting the car?

34:53.827 --> 34:55.326
It's hard laying down back here.

34:55.327 --> 34:57.326
Mother, get back down, now.

34:57.327 --> 34:59.496
The people I was having dinner
with are just a few cars away.

34:59.497 --> 35:01.286
They might see you.

35:01.287 --> 35:03.906
- Bye.
- Bye.

35:03.907 --> 35:07.996
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:07.997 --> 35:10.246
(CAR DOOR CLOSES, ENGINE TURNING OVER)

35:10.947 --> 35:12.286
She looks like me.

35:12.287 --> 35:14.465
Why are you having dinner with
someone who looks like me?

35:14.466 --> 35:15.496
I don't think she looks like you.

35:15.497 --> 35:17.246
She's like me but ten years younger.

35:17.247 --> 35:18.366
(VEHICLE DEPARTING)

35:18.367 --> 35:20.206
Are you gonna be one of those guys?

35:20.207 --> 35:23.036
Mother, it was just a
friendly little dinner.

35:23.037 --> 35:26.366
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:26.367 --> 35:27.996
- What are you doing?
- I'm going out.

35:27.997 --> 35:30.826
- No, Mother. You can't.
- Can't I?

35:30.827 --> 35:33.666
(LOUNGE-Y FRENCH MUSIC PLAYING)

35:33.667 --> 35:40.496
♪ ♪

35:40.497 --> 35:42.406
Bourbon, neat.

35:42.407 --> 35:49.287
♪ ♪

35:58.259 --> 35:59.588
How's your night going?

35:59.589 --> 36:00.706
Oh, it's going.

36:00.707 --> 36:02.996
♪ ♪

36:02.997 --> 36:04.787
I'm just sick of my job.

36:06.413 --> 36:07.906
I hear you.

36:08.388 --> 36:09.476
What do you do?

36:09.477 --> 36:13.456
♪ ♪

36:13.878 --> 36:16.537
I'm a caretaker for a
mentally ill person.

36:16.538 --> 36:18.627
♪ ♪

36:18.628 --> 36:19.917
Wow.

36:19.918 --> 36:21.600
That's a tough gig.

36:21.601 --> 36:23.364
Yeah, you're not kidding.

36:23.365 --> 36:24.948
♪ ♪

36:24.949 --> 36:27.773
And I don't... I don't think
he likes me that much anymore.

36:28.349 --> 36:30.048
It makes the job a lot harder.

36:30.049 --> 36:31.968
I'm like, "What the hell
am I doing this for?"

36:31.969 --> 36:34.258
"Personal satisfaction?" (SCOFFS)

36:34.259 --> 36:35.968
♪ ♪

36:35.969 --> 36:38.388
I spend a lot of time alone

36:38.389 --> 36:40.468
or getting him out of
problems he creates...

36:40.469 --> 36:42.138
By not listening to me, you know?

36:42.139 --> 36:44.548
And... and... (SIGHS)

36:44.549 --> 36:46.968
I just don't like having
to do these things.

36:46.969 --> 36:48.348
It's getting to me.

36:48.349 --> 36:49.758
♪ ♪

36:49.759 --> 36:52.699
I need to get out more, see real people.

36:54.259 --> 36:57.008
I'm gonna have to start
cutting my hours.

36:57.009 --> 36:58.795
I admire that you do that work.

36:59.527 --> 37:02.004
I'm sure it means a lot to the
guy you're taking care of,

37:02.599 --> 37:04.928
even if he can't articulate it.

37:04.929 --> 37:07.468
♪ ♪

37:07.469 --> 37:08.928
He can't.

37:08.929 --> 37:09.928
♪ ♪

37:09.929 --> 37:11.548
Not lately.

37:11.549 --> 37:18.469
♪ ♪

37:19.849 --> 37:21.218
Hit me.

37:21.219 --> 37:27.468
♪ ♪

37:27.469 --> 37:31.638
<i>Even though she wasn't
there, except in his mind.</i>

37:31.639 --> 37:34.848
<i>She was dead, but what did that matter?</i>

37:34.849 --> 37:37.508
<i>How different is that
from any relationship?</i>

37:37.509 --> 37:41.178
<i>How much do we project onto our mates?</i>

37:41.179 --> 37:44.678
<i>And why the hell do we
need so much anyways?</i>

37:44.679 --> 37:46.178
<i>Is happiness, in a sense,</i>

37:46.179 --> 37:48.258
<i>all just a creation of the mind?</i>

37:48.259 --> 37:51.718
(DOOR OPENS, CREAKS)

37:51.719 --> 37:54.138
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

37:54.139 --> 37:56.218
- Double Scotch.
- You got it.

37:56.219 --> 37:59.178
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

37:59.179 --> 38:06.099
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:08.509 --> 38:12.138
Of all the gin joints in all the towns

38:12.139 --> 38:14.218
in all the world...

38:14.219 --> 38:21.139
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:23.719 --> 38:26.542
Look, don't mess with me.

38:27.881 --> 38:29.808
You don't want to mess
with me right now.

38:29.809 --> 38:32.388
That's funny.

38:32.389 --> 38:33.848
You're saying that to somebody

38:33.849 --> 38:36.013
who you beat the crap out of,

38:36.549 --> 38:38.468
left for dead, stole all their money,

38:38.469 --> 38:39.968
and ruined their life.

38:39.969 --> 38:42.258
- (CHUCKLES) That's funny.
- Yeah, funny.

38:42.259 --> 38:43.542
You're forgetting about the part

38:43.543 --> 38:45.548
where you almost got
me and my son killed.

38:45.549 --> 38:48.468
Dylan. Norma's kid.

38:48.469 --> 38:51.717
(SOFT ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

38:51.718 --> 38:53.009
Your kid.

38:53.679 --> 38:57.178
Don't you dare talk about her like that,

38:57.179 --> 38:58.848
or I will kill you.

38:58.849 --> 39:01.548
♪ ♪

39:01.549 --> 39:04.008
I'm sorry.

39:04.009 --> 39:06.888
We don't have to talk about
how you raped your sister.

39:06.889 --> 39:08.308
(GLASS BREAKING)

39:08.309 --> 39:11.428
I don't care if we are in public, okay?

39:11.429 --> 39:14.598
You say her name again like that,

39:14.599 --> 39:16.388
and I will kill you.

39:16.389 --> 39:18.138
I will kill you.

39:18.139 --> 39:20.718
Okay. Good, good.

39:20.719 --> 39:27.309
♪ ♪

39:30.049 --> 39:33.468
(GROANS)

39:33.469 --> 39:35.468
Holy shit.

39:35.469 --> 39:38.138
<i>(SOMBER MUSIC)</i>

39:38.139 --> 39:39.928
You just found out.

39:39.929 --> 39:42.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:42.929 --> 39:44.428
Just leave me the hell alone, all right?

39:44.429 --> 39:46.508
- You have no idea about anything.
- Wait.

39:46.509 --> 39:47.718
(DOOR OPENS)

39:47.719 --> 39:48.968
Wait!

39:48.969 --> 39:51.437
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:51.438 --> 39:53.728
She wouldn't kill herself.

39:54.179 --> 39:55.863
I told her.

39:57.099 --> 39:58.678
- You told who?
- Norma.

39:58.679 --> 40:00.428
I warned her about her kid.

40:00.429 --> 40:02.678
- What about Norman?
- I told her...

40:02.679 --> 40:04.679
he was gonna snap someday.

40:04.680 --> 40:05.848
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:05.849 --> 40:07.546
She didn't listen to me.

40:08.349 --> 40:10.931
Maybe you don't know Norman the
way that you think you do.

40:10.932 --> 40:12.388
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:12.389 --> 40:14.548
He's not getting away with it, no.

40:14.549 --> 40:17.259
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:19.266 --> 40:22.136
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

40:29.766 --> 40:32.725
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

40:32.726 --> 40:39.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:08.186 --> 41:15.265
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:15.266 --> 41:18.135
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC SWELLS)</i>

41:18.136 --> 41:24.976
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:40.809 --> 41:42.808
Norman!

41:42.809 --> 41:49.018
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:49.019 --> 41:51.018
Shit!

41:51.019 --> 41:55.348
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:55.349 --> 41:57.018
Norman!

41:57.019 --> 41:58.598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:58.599 --> 42:00.518
You're not getting away!

42:00.519 --> 42:07.469
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:11.429 --> 42:13.348
I know what you did!

42:13.349 --> 42:14.848
Norman!

42:14.849 --> 42:21.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:31.389 --> 42:33.558
Norman!

42:33.559 --> 42:40.429
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:51.889 --> 42:54.848
<i>(DARK MUSIC)</i>

42:54.849 --> 43:00.598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:00.599 --> 43:03.388
Holy shit.

43:03.389 --> 43:09.258
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:09.259 --> 43:11.218
Well, now you know, Chick.

43:11.219 --> 43:13.638
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:13.639 --> 43:15.428
I'm still alive.

